{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884623063,"sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","part":{"id":"prt_d7af8d468001oKBcFeu5DNC1Ep","messageID":"msg_d7af8b8b6001mDOtd5gsCpruZm","sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-344690ef824c404aa494cad1aafbdda5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Define the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                         Helm Chart Structure                                 │\n24: │                     manifests/charts/base/                                   │\n25: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐      │\n28: │  │   Chart.yaml     │    │   values.yaml    │    │  templates/_*    │      │\n29: │  │  (Metadata)      │───▶│  (Config)        │───▶│  (Rendered YAML) │      │\n30: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘      │\n31: │                                                                              │\n32: │  Templates:                                                                  │\n33: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n34: │  │ workloadmanager.yaml        │ Deployment + Service                   │    │\n35: │  │ agentcube-router.yaml       │ Deployment + Service                   │    │\n36: │  │ rbac/workloadmanager.yaml   │ SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding   │    │\n37: │  │ rbac-router.yaml            │ SA, Role, RoleBinding (conditional)   │    │\n38: │  │ volcano-agent-scheduler     │ Scheduler resources (conditional)      │    │\n39: │  │ _helpers.tpl                │ Named template helpers                 │    │\n40: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n41: │                                                                              │\n42: │  CRDs (crds/):                                                               │\n43: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n44: │  │ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml                      │    │\n45: │  │ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml                   │    │\n46: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n47: │                                                                              │\n48: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Deployment Model\n52: \n53: ```\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                                       │\n56: │                      Namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}                     │\n57: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n58: │                                                                              │\n59: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n60: │  │                    AgentCube Components                                 │ │\n61: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n62: │  │                                                                         │ │\n63: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐         ┌───────────────────┐                  │ │\n64: │  │  │ workloadmanager   │         │ agentcube-router  │                  │ │\n65: │  │  │ Deployment        │◀───────▶│ Deployment        │                  │ │\n66: │  │  │ (replicas: 1)     │         │ (replicas: 1)     │                  │ │\n67: │  │  │ Port: 8080        │         │ Port: 8080        │                  │ │\n68: │  │  └───────────────────┘         └───────────────────┘                  │ │\n69: │  │          │                              │                              │ │\n70: │  │          │                              │                              │ │\n71: │  │          ▼                              ▼                              │ │\n72: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐         ┌───────────────────┐                  │ │\n73: │  │  │ workloadmanager   │         │ agentcube-router  │                  │ │\n74: │  │  │ Service (ClusterIP│         │ Service (ClusterIP│                  │ │\n75: │  │  │  port: 8080)      │         │  port: 8080)      │                  │ │\n76: │  │  └───────────────────┘         └───────────────────┘                  │ │\n77: │  │                                                                         │ │\n78: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐                                                │ │\n79: │  │  │ redis Deployment  │    (if enabled, external or bundled)          │ │\n80: │  │  │ redis Service     │                                                │ │\n81: │  │  │ Port: 6379        │                                                │ │\n82: │  │  └───────────────────┘                                                │ │\n83: │  │                                                                         │ │\n84: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐                                                │ │\n85: │  │  │ volcano-agent-    │    (if volcano.scheduler.enabled)             │ │\n86: │  │  │ scheduler         │                                                │ │\n87: │  │  └───────────────────┘                                                │ │\n88: │  │                                                                         │ │\n89: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n90: │                                                                              │\n91: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n92: │  │                    RBAC Resources                                       │ │\n93: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n94: │  │  ServiceAccount: workloadmanager (cluster-scoped)                      │ │\n95: │  │  ServiceAccount: agentcube-router (namespace-scoped, conditional)      │ │\n96: │  │  ServiceAccount: volcano-agent-scheduler (cluster-scoped, conditional) │ │\n97: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n98: │                                                                              │\n99: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n100: │  │                    Secrets                                              │ │\n101: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n102: │  │  jwt-secret: JWT signing key (optional)                                │ │\n103: │  │  identity-secret: Picod-Router identity (optional)                     │ │\n104: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n105: │                                                                              │\n106: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### Component Relationships\n110: \n111: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n112: |-----------|------|--------------|\n113: | `Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) | None |\n114: | `values.yaml` | Default configuration values | Chart.yaml (version reference) |\n115: | `_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers (name, fullname, labels) | values.yaml |\n116: | `workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl |\n117: | `agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl, workloadmanager Service |\n118: | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | RBAC for WorkloadManager | _helpers.tpl, workloadmanager.yaml |\n119: | `rbac-router.yaml` | RBAC for Router (conditional) | _helpers.tpl, agentcube-router.yaml |\n120: | `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Volcano scheduler (conditional) | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl |\n121: | `crds/*.yaml` | CRD definitions (installed before templates) | controller-gen |\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Data Structures\n126: \n127: ### Chart.yaml Schema\n128: \n129: ```yaml\n130: apiVersion: v1\n131: name: agentcube\n132: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n133: type: application\n134: version: 0.1.0        # Chart version (SemVer 2)\n135: appVersion: 1.0.0     # Application version\n136: keywords:\n137:   - agentcube\n138:   - kubernetes\n139:   - sandbox\n140:   - ai-agents\n141: maintainers:\n142:   - name: volcano-sh\n143:     email: volcano-sh@example.com\n144: sources:\n145:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ### values.yaml Schema\n149: \n150: ```yaml\n151: # Global settings\n152: imagePullSecrets: []           # array[string] - Secret names for private registries\n153: nameOverride: \"\"               # string - Partial name override\n154: fullnameOverride: \"\"           # string - Full name override\n155: \n156: # Redis connection (must be provided by user)\n157: redis:\n158:   addr: \"\"                     # string - Redis address (host:port)\n159:   password: \"\"                 # string - Redis password (empty = no auth)\n160: \n161: # WorkloadManager configuration\n162: workloadmanager:\n163:   replicas: 1                  # int - Deployment replicas\n164:   image:\n165:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n166:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n167:     tag: latest\n168:   service:\n169:     type: ClusterIP\n170:     port: 8080\n171:   resources:\n172:     limits:\n173:       cpu: 500m\n174:       memory: 512Mi\n175:     requests:\n176:       cpu: 100m\n177:       memory: 128Mi\n178:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n179: \n180: # Router configuration\n181: router:\n182:   replicas: 1\n183:   image:\n184:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n185:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n186:     tag: latest\n187:   service:\n188:     type: ClusterIP\n189:     port: 8080\n190:     targetPort: 8080\n191:   resources:\n192:     limits:\n193:       cpu: 500m\n194:       memory: 512Mi\n195:     requests:\n196:       cpu: 100m\n197:       memory: 128Mi\n198:   config: {}                   # object - Router configuration\n199:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n200:   serviceAccountName: \"\"       # string - ServiceAccount name (empty = default)\n201:   rbac:\n202:     create: false              # bool - Create RBAC resources\n203: \n204: # Volcano scheduler (optional)\n205: volcano:\n206:   scheduler:\n207:     enabled: false             # bool - Enable Volcano agent scheduler\n208:     replicas: 1\n209:     image:\n210:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n211:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n212:       tag: latest\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ### Values Type Definitions\n216: \n217: | Path | Type | Default | Description |\n218: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n219: | `imagePullSecrets` | `array[string]` | `[]` | Secret names for private registries |\n220: | `nameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Partial name override |\n221: | `fullnameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Full name override |\n222: | `redis.addr` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis address (`host:port`) |\n223: | `redis.password` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis password |\n224: | `router.replicas` | `int` | `1` | Router deployment replicas |\n225: | `router.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | Router image repository |\n226: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | `string` | `IfNotPresent` | Image pull policy |\n227: | `router.image.tag` | `string` | `latest` | Router image tag |\n228: | `router.service.type` | `string` | `ClusterIP` | Router service type |\n229: | `router.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | Router service port |\n230: | `router.service.targetPort` | `int` | `8080` | Router container port |\n231: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | `string` | `500m` | CPU limit |\n232: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | `string` | `512Mi` | Memory limit |\n233: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | `string` | `100m` | CPU request |\n234: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | `string` | `128Mi` | Memory request |\n235: | `router.serviceAccountName` | `string` | `\"\"` | ServiceAccount name |\n236: | `router.rbac.create` | `bool` | `false` | Create Router RBAC |\n237: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | `int` | `1` | WorkloadManager replicas |\n238: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | WorkloadManager image |\n239: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | WorkloadManager service port |\n240: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | `bool` | `false` | Enable Volcano scheduler |\n241: \n242: ### Named Templates (_helpers.tpl)\n243: \n244: ```yaml\n245: {{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n246: {{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n247: {{- end -}}\n248: \n249: {{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n250: {{- if .Values.fullnameOverride -}}\n251: {{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n252: {{- else -}}\n253: {{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride -}}\n254: {{- if contains $name .Release.Name -}}\n255: {{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n256: {{- else -}}\n257: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n258: {{- end -}}\n259: {{- end -}}\n260: {{- end -}}\n261: \n262: {{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\n263: app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n264: app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n265: app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n266: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n267: {{- end -}}\n268: \n269: {{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\n270: app: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n271: {{- end -}}\n272: \n273: {{- define \"agentcube.image\" -}}\n274: {{- $registry := .Values.global.imageRegistry | default \"\" -}}\n275: {{- $repository := .repository -}}\n276: {{- $tag := .tag | default \"latest\" -}}\n277: {{- if $registry -}}\n278: {{- printf \"%s/%s:%s\" $registry $repository $tag -}}\n279: {{- else -}}\n280: {{- printf \"%s:%s\" $repository $tag -}}\n281: {{- end -}}\n282: {{- end -}}\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## API Contracts\n288: \n289: ### WorkloadManager Deployment Template\n290: \n291: ```yaml\n292: apiVersion: apps/v1\n293: kind: Deployment\n294: metadata:\n295:   name: workloadmanager\n296:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n297:   labels:\n298:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n299: spec:\n300:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n301:   selector:\n302:     matchLabels:\n303:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n304:       app: workloadmanager\n305:   template:\n306:     metadata:\n307:       labels:\n308:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n309:         app: workloadmanager\n310:     spec:\n311:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n312:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n313:       imagePullSecrets:\n314:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n315:       {{- end }}\n316:       containers:\n317:         - name: workloadmanager\n318:           image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"\n319:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n320:           ports:\n321:             - name: http\n322:               containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n323:               protocol: TCP\n324:           env:\n325:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n326:               valueFrom:\n327:                 fieldRef:\n328:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n329:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n330:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n331:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n332:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n333:             {{- with .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}\n334:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n335:             {{- end }}\n336:           args:\n337:             - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n338:             - --runtime-class-name=\n339:           resources:\n340:             {{- toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 12 }}\n341:           livenessProbe:\n342:             httpGet:\n343:               path: /health\n344:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n345:             initialDelaySeconds: 10\n346:             periodSeconds: 10\n347:           readinessProbe:\n348:             httpGet:\n349:               path: /health\n350:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n351:             initialDelaySeconds: 5\n352:             periodSeconds: 5\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### WorkloadManager Service Template\n356: \n357: ```yaml\n358: apiVersion: v1\n359: kind: Service\n360: metadata:\n361:   name: workloadmanager\n362:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n363:   labels:\n364:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n365: spec:\n366:   type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n367:   ports:\n368:     - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n369:       targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n370:       protocol: TCP\n371:       name: http\n372:   selector:\n373:     app: workloadmanager\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### Router Deployment Template\n377: \n378: ```yaml\n379: apiVersion: apps/v1\n380: kind: Deployment\n381: metadata:\n382:   name: agentcube-router\n383:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n384:   labels:\n385:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n386: spec:\n387:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n388:   selector:\n389:     matchLabels:\n390:       app: agentcube-router\n391:   template:\n392:     metadata:\n393:       labels:\n394:         app: agentcube-router\n395:     spec:\n396:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n397:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n398:       {{- end }}\n399:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n400:       imagePullSecrets:\n401:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n402:       {{- end }}\n403:       containers:\n404:         - name: agentcube-router\n405:           image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"\n406:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n407:           ports:\n408:             - name: http\n409:               containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n410:               protocol: TCP\n411:           env:\n412:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n413:               valueFrom:\n414:                 fieldRef:\n415:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n416:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n417:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n418:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n419:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n420:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n421:               value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n422:             {{- with .Values.router.extraEnv }}\n423:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n424:             {{- end }}\n425:           args:\n426:             - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n427:             - --debug\n428:           resources:\n429:             {{- toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 12 }}\n430:           livenessProbe:\n431:             httpGet:\n432:               path: /health/live\n433:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n434:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n435:             periodSeconds: 2\n436:           readinessProbe:\n437:             httpGet:\n438:               path: /health/ready\n439:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n440:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n441:             periodSeconds: 2\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### Router Service Template\n445: \n446: ```yaml\n447: apiVersion: v1\n448: kind: Service\n449: metadata:\n450:   name: agentcube-router\n451:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n452:   labels:\n453:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n454: spec:\n455:   type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n456:   ports:\n457:     - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n458:       targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n459:       protocol: TCP\n460:       name: http\n461:   selector:\n462:     app: agentcube-router\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ---\n466: \n467: ## Error Handling\n468: \n469: ### Template Validation Errors\n470: \n471: | Error Type | Cause | Resolution |\n472: |------------|-------|------------|\n473: | `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax or missing required fields | Fix template syntax, add required fields |\n474: | `Render error` | Undefined template reference or invalid values path | Check helper template names, validate values paths |\n475: | `Missing value` | Required value not provided | Set required values in values.yaml or via `--set` |\n476: | `Invalid resource spec` | Kubernetes API schema violation | Validate against Kubernetes API schema |\n477: \n478: ### Validation Patterns\n479: \n480: ```yaml\n481: {{- if not .Values.redis.addr }}\n482: {{- fail \"redis.addr must be provided\" }}\n483: {{- end }}\n484: \n485: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n486: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n487: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n488: {{- end }}\n489: {{- end }}\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Conditional Rendering\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n496: # RBAC resources rendered\n497: {{- end }}\n498: \n499: {{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}\n500: # Volcano scheduler resources rendered\n501: {{- end }}\n502: \n503: {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n504: imagePullSecrets:\n505:   {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n506: {{- end }}\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Testing Strategy\n512: \n513: ### Test Categories\n514: \n515: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n516: |----------|-------|-------|\n517: | Helm lint | Chart syntax validation | `helm lint manifests/charts/base` |\n518: | Template render | YAML output validation | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` |\n519: | Values override | Custom values integration | `helm template ... -f custom-values.yaml` |\n520: | E2E deployment | Full stack deployment | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n521: | CRD validation | CRD schema compliance | `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` |\n522: \n523: ### Helm Lint Tests\n524: \n525: ```bash\n526: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n527: # Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n528: ```\n529: \n530: ### Template Render Tests\n531: \n532: ```bash\n533: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n534:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n535:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n536:   > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n537: \n538: # Validate rendered YAML\n539: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ### Values Override Tests\n543: \n544: ```yaml\n545: # test-values.yaml\n546: redis:\n547:   addr: \"redis.test.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n548:   password: \"test-password\"\n549: router:\n550:   replicas: 2\n551:   rbac:\n552:     create: true\n553:   serviceAccountName: \"test-router-sa\"\n554: workloadmanager:\n555:   replicas: 3\n556:   extraEnv:\n557:     - name: TEST_ENV\n558:       value: \"test-value\"\n559: ```\n560: \n561: ```bash\n562: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f test-values.yaml\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ### E2E Integration Test\n566: \n567: ```bash\n568: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n569:   --namespace agentcube \\\n570:   --create-namespace \\\n571:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n572:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n573:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n574:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n575:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n576:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n577:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n578:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n579:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n580:   --wait\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ### Test Matrix\n584: \n585: | Test Case | Values Override | Expected Output |\n586: |-----------|-----------------|-----------------|\n587: | Default values | None | All components enabled with defaults |\n588: | Router RBAC enabled | `router.rbac.create=true` | Router RBAC resources rendered |\n589: | Volcano scheduler enabled | `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` | Scheduler resources rendered |\n590: | Custom replicas | `router.replicas=3` | Router Deployment spec.replicas=3 |\n591: | Custom resources | `router.resources.limits.cpu=1` | CPU limit overridden |\n592: | Extra environment | `router.extraEnv=[{...}]` | Additional env vars rendered |\n593: | Image override | `router.image.tag=v1.0.0` | Custom image tag used |\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## File Structure\n598: \n599: | Path | Role |\n600: |------|------|\n601: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) |\n602: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n603: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers |\n604: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n605: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service |\n606: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager RBAC (SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n607: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router RBAC (SA, Role, RoleBinding - conditional) |\n608: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n609: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | AgentRuntime CRD |\n610: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | CodeInterpreter CRD |\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Dependencies\n615: \n616: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n617: |---------|---------|---------|\n618: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n619: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD |\n620: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n621: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## Implementation Notes\n626: \n627: ### RBAC Rules\n628: \n629: #### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n630: \n631: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n632: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n633: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n634: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n635: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n636: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n637: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n638: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n639: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n640: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n641: | `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n642: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n643: | `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n644: \n645: #### Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n646: \n647: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n648: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n649: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n650: \n651: ### Health Probes\n652: \n653: | Component | Liveness Path | Readiness Path | Initial Delay | Period |\n654: |-----------|---------------|----------------|---------------|--------|\n655: | WorkloadManager | `/health` | `/health` | 10s / 5s | 10s / 5s |\n656: | Router | `/health/live` | `/health/ready` | 1s | 2s |\n657: \n658: ### Environment Variables\n659: \n660: | Variable | Source | Component |\n661: |----------|--------|-----------|\n662: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n663: | `REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n664: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n665: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Constructed from release namespace | Router |\n666: \n667: ### CRD Schema\n668: \n669: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n670: \n671: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n672: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n673: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | Yes |\n674: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | Yes |\n675: | `podTemplate` | object | - | Yes |\n676: | `targetPort` | array | - | Yes |\n677: \n678: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n679: \n680: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n681: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n682: | `authMode` | enum (`picod`, `none`) | `picod` | No |\n683: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | No |\n684: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | No |\n685: | `template` | object | - | Yes |\n686: | `warmPoolSize` | int32 | - | No |\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ## References\n691: \n692: - Spec: `changes/AR-030/spec.md`\n693: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`\n694: - Proposal: `changes/AR-030/proposal.md`\n695: - Tasks: `changes/AR-030/tasks.md`\n696: - deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n697: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n698: - project.md — AgentCube project context\n699: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n700: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n\n(End of file - total 700 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775884623024,"end":1775884623060}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884623067,"sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","part":{"id":"prt_d7af8d8600018ju3BKhbyuPZyC","messageID":"msg_d7af8b8b6001mDOtd5gsCpruZm","sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-df2699343df34a35b7c21781d040ab43","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Chart Foundation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with chart metadata\n20:   - Purpose: Define chart name, version, appVersion, and metadata\n21:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n22:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with default configuration\n25:   - Purpose: Define default values for all configurable parameters\n26:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n27:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` with named templates\n30:   - Purpose: Define helper templates for name, fullname, labels, selectorLabels, image\n31:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl`\n32:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"app.kubernetes.io/name\"`\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: WorkloadManager Templates (ST-2)\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `workloadmanager.yaml` Deployment template\n37:   - Purpose: Define WorkloadManager Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources\n38:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n39:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: Deployment\" | head -1`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment container ports configuration\n42:   - Purpose: Configure container port from `workloadmanager.service.port`\n43:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n44:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.service.port=9090 | grep \"containerPort: 9090\"`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment environment variables\n47:   - Purpose: Inject AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE, REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD from values\n48:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n49:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.test:6379\" --set redis.password=\"secret\" | grep \"REDIS_ADDR\"`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment resources configuration\n52:   - Purpose: Configure CPU/memory limits and requests from `workloadmanager.resources`\n53:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n54:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu=1 | grep \"cpu: 1\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment health probes\n57:   - Purpose: Add livenessProbe and readinessProbe for /health endpoint\n58:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"livenessProbe\"`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment extraEnv support\n62:   - Purpose: Allow additional environment variables via `workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n63:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"TEST\",\"value\":\"val\"}]' | grep \"name: TEST\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager Service template\n67:   - Purpose: Define ClusterIP Service for WorkloadManager\n68:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: Service\"`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement WorkloadManager Service port configuration\n72:   - Purpose: Configure service port from `workloadmanager.service.port`\n73:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.service.port=9090 | grep \"port: 9090\"`\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: Router Templates (ST-3)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `agentcube-router.yaml` Deployment template\n79:   - Purpose: Define Router Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources\n80:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n81:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"name: agentcube-router\"`\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement Router Deployment container ports configuration\n84:   - Purpose: Configure container port from `router.service.targetPort`\n85:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n86:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.service.targetPort=9090 | grep \"containerPort: 9090\"`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement Router Deployment environment variables\n89:   - Purpose: Inject AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE, REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n90:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n91:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.test:6379\" --namespace test | grep \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement Router Deployment resources configuration\n94:   - Purpose: Configure CPU/memory limits and requests from `router.resources`\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n96:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.resources.limits.memory=1Gi | grep \"memory: 1Gi\"`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement Router Deployment health probes\n99:   - Purpose: Add livenessProbe (/health/live) and readinessProbe (/health/ready)\n100:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n101:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"path: /health/live\"`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement Router Deployment serviceAccountName support\n104:   - Purpose: Allow custom ServiceAccount via `router.serviceAccountName`\n105:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n106:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T3.7**: Implement Router Deployment extraEnv support\n109:   - Purpose: Allow additional environment variables via `router.extraEnv`\n110:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n111:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"DEBUG\",\"value\":\"true\"}]' | grep \"name: DEBUG\"`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T3.8**: Create Router Service template\n114:   - Purpose: Define ClusterIP Service for Router\n115:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n116:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: agentcube-router\" | grep \"kind: Service\"`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.9**: Implement Router Service port configuration\n119:   - Purpose: Configure service port and targetPort from values\n120:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n121:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.service.port=80 | grep \"port: 80\"`\n122: \n123: ### Phase 4: RBAC Templates (ST-4)\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` ServiceAccount\n126:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped)\n127:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n128:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\"`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T4.2**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole with full permissions\n131:   - Purpose: Define ClusterRole with permissions for agents.x-k8s.io, runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, pods, secrets\n132:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n133:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.3**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n136:   - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount\n137:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n138:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.4**: Create `templates/rbac-router.yaml` with conditional rendering\n141:   - Purpose: Define Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) when `router.rbac.create=true`\n142:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n143:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=router-sa | grep \"kind: Role\"`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement Router Role with secrets permissions\n146:   - Purpose: Define namespace-scoped Role with secrets permissions\n147:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n148:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true | grep \"apiGroups:.*core\"`\n149: \n150: ### Phase 5: Volcano Scheduler Templates (ST-5)\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` with conditional rendering\n153:   - Purpose: Define Volcano scheduler resources when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n154:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n155:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true | grep \"vc-agent-scheduler\"`\n156: \n157: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement Volcano scheduler Deployment template\n158:   - Purpose: Define scheduler Deployment with configurable image and replicas\n159:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n160:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true | grep \"kind: Deployment\"`\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount and RBAC\n163:   - Purpose: Define cluster-scoped ServiceAccount and ClusterRole for scheduler\n164:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n165:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true | grep \"ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n166: \n167: ### Phase 6: CRD Definitions (ST-6)\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n170:   - Purpose: Define AgentRuntime CRD schema\n171:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n172:   - Verification: `kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T6.2**: Define AgentRuntime CRD spec with maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, podTemplate, targetPort\n175:   - Purpose: Configure AgentRuntime CRD fields\n176:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n177:   - Verification: `grep \"maxSessionDuration\" manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T6.3**: Create `crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n180:   - Purpose: Define CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n181:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n182:   - Verification: `kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n183: \n184: - [ ] **T6.4**: Define CodeInterpreter CRD spec with authMode, maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, template, warmPoolSize\n185:   - Purpose: Configure CodeInterpreter CRD fields\n186:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n187:   - Verification: `grep \"authMode\" manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 7: Template Validation & Fail Guards (ST-7)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.1**: Implement redis.addr required value validation\n192:   - Purpose: Fail template render if redis.addr not provided\n193:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl`\n194:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base 2>&1 | grep \"redis.addr must be provided\"`\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.2**: Implement router.rbac.create + serviceAccountName validation\n197:   - Purpose: Fail if rbac.create=true but serviceAccountName not set\n198:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n199:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T7.3**: Implement imagePullSecrets conditional rendering\n202:   - Purpose: Only render imagePullSecrets when values are provided\n203:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`, `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n204:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -c \"imagePullSecrets\" || echo \"0\"`\n205: \n206: ### Phase 8: Helm Chart Tests (ST-8)\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T8.1**: Run Helm lint on chart with default values\n209:   - Purpose: Validate chart syntax and structure\n210:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n211:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"`\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T8.2**: Run Helm template with custom replicas\n214:   - Purpose: Verify replicas override works for router and workloadmanager\n215:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n216:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.replicas=3 | grep \"replicas: 3\"`\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T8.3**: Run Helm template with custom resources\n219:   - Purpose: Verify resource overrides work\n220:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n221:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.resources.limits.cpu=2 | grep \"cpu: 2\"`\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T8.4**: Run Helm template with router RBAC enabled\n224:   - Purpose: Verify conditional RBAC rendering\n225:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n226:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: Role\"`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T8.5**: Run Helm template with Volcano scheduler enabled\n229:   - Purpose: Verify conditional scheduler rendering\n230:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n231:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true | grep \"vc-agent-scheduler\"`\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T8.6**: Validate rendered YAML with kubectl dry-run\n234:   - Purpose: Verify rendered manifests are valid Kubernetes resources\n235:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n236:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml`\n237: \n238: - [ ] **T8.7**: Test extraEnv injection for WorkloadManager\n239:   - Purpose: Verify extra environment variables are rendered\n240:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n241:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"CUSTOM\",\"value\":\"test\"}]' | grep \"name: CUSTOM\"`\n242: \n243: - [ ] **T8.8**: Test extraEnv injection for Router\n244:   - Purpose: Verify extra environment variables are rendered\n245:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n246:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"LOG_LEVEL\",\"value\":\"debug\"}]' | grep \"name: LOG_LEVEL\"`\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## Task Dependencies\n251: \n252: ```\n253: Phase 1 (Foundation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n254: T1.1 (Chart.yaml) ──┬── T1.2 (values.yaml)\n255:                    └── T1.3 (_helpers.tpl)\n256:                               ├── T2.1 (workloadmanager Deployment)\n257:                               ├── T3.1 (router Deployment)\n258:                               ├── T4.1-T4.5 (RBAC templates)\n259:                               └── T5.1-T5.3 (Volcano scheduler)\n260:                               └── T7.1 (validation)\n261: \n262: Phase 2 (WorkloadManager) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n263: T2.1 ──┬── T2.2 (container ports)\n264:        ├── T2.3 (env vars)\n265:        ├── T2.4 (resources)\n266:        ├── T2.5 (health probes)\n267:        ├── T2.6 (extraEnv)\n268:        └── T2.7-T2.8 (Service)\n269: \n270: Phase 3 (Router) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n271: T3.1 ──┬── T3.2 (container ports)\n272:        ├── T3.3 (env vars)\n273:        ├── T3.4 (resources)\n274:        ├── T3.5 (health probes)\n275:        ├── T3.6 (serviceAccountName)\n276:        ├── T3.7 (extraEnv)\n277:        └── T3.8-T3.9 (Service)\n278: \n279: Phase 4 (RBAC) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n280: T1.3 ──┬── T4.1 (WorkloadManager SA)\n281:        ├── T4.2 (ClusterRole)\n282:        ├── T4.3 (ClusterRoleBinding)\n283:        └── T4.4-T4.5 (Router RBAC - conditional)\n284: \n285: Phase 5 (Volcano Scheduler) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n286: T1.3 ──┬── T5.1 (conditional rendering)\n287:        ├── T5.2 (Deployment)\n288:        └── T5.3 (RBAC)\n289: \n290: Phase 6 (CRDs) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n291: T6.1 ──┬── T6.2 (AgentRuntime spec)\n292: T6.3 ──┬── T6.4 (CodeInterpreter spec)\n293: \n294: Phase 7 (Validation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n295: T1.2, T1.3 ──┬── T7.1 (redis.addr validation)\n296: T4.4 ───────┬── T7.2 (rbac validation)\n297: T2.1, T3.1 ─┬── T7.3 (imagePullSecrets conditional)\n298: \n299: Phase 8 (Tests) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n300: T1.1-T7.3 ──┬── T8.1-T8.8 (all tests)\n301: ```\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Verification Commands\n306: \n307: | Task | Verification Command |\n308: |------|----------------------|\n309: | Phase 1 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"` |\n310: | Phase 2 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"name: workloadmanager\"` |\n311: | Phase 3 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"name: agentcube-router\"` |\n312: | Phase 4 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: Role\"` |\n313: | Phase 5 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true | grep \"vc-agent-scheduler\"` |\n314: | Phase 6 | `kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n315: | Phase 7 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base 2>&1` (should fail without redis.addr) |\n316: | Phase 8 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" && helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml` |\n317: \n318: ---\n319: \n320: ## Acceptance Criteria\n321: \n322: - [ ] `Chart.yaml` with name, version, appVersion, description, keywords, maintainers, sources\n323: - [ ] `values.yaml` with redis.addr, redis.password, imagePullSecrets, nameOverride, fullnameOverride\n324: - [ ] `values.yaml` with workloadmanager.* (replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv)\n325: - [ ] `values.yaml` with router.* (replicas, image, service, resources, config, extraEnv, serviceAccountName, rbac.create)\n326: - [ ] `values.yaml` with volcano.scheduler.* (enabled, replicas, image)\n327: - [ ] `_helpers.tpl` with agentcube.name, agentcube.fullname, agentcube.labels, agentcube.selectorLabels, agentcube.image\n328: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment template with configurable replicas, image, resources, env, probes\n329: - [ ] WorkloadManager Service template with configurable type and port\n330: - [ ] Router Deployment template with configurable replicas, image, resources, env, probes, serviceAccountName\n331: - [ ] Router Service template with configurable port and targetPort\n332: - [ ] WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) with full permissions\n333: - [ ] Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) conditionally rendered\n334: - [ ] Volcano scheduler resources conditionally rendered\n335: - [ ] AgentRuntime CRD with maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, podTemplate, targetPort\n336: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD with authMode, maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, template, warmPoolSize\n337: - [ ] Template fails if redis.addr not provided\n338: - [ ] Template fails if router.rbac.create=true but serviceAccountName not set\n339: - [ ] imagePullSecrets only rendered when values are provided\n340: - [ ] Helm lint passes with 0 errors\n341: - [ ] Rendered YAML validates with kubectl dry-run\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## File Changes Summary\n346: \n347: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n348: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n349: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Create | ~20 | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) |\n350: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Create | ~80 | Default configuration values |\n351: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Create | ~50 | Named template helpers |\n352: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | ~100 | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n353: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Create | ~100 | Router Deployment + Service |\n354: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | ~80 | WorkloadManager RBAC (SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n355: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Create | ~50 | Router RBAC (conditional) |\n356: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Create | ~60 | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n357: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | Create | ~150 | AgentRuntime CRD |\n358: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | Create | ~150 | CodeInterpreter CRD |\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## Implementation Notes\n363: \n364: ### Chart.yaml Structure\n365: \n366: ```yaml\n367: apiVersion: v1\n368: name: agentcube\n369: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n370: type: application\n371: version: 0.1.0\n372: appVersion: 1.0.0\n373: keywords:\n374:   - agentcube\n375:   - kubernetes\n376:   - sandbox\n377:   - ai-agents\n378: maintainers:\n379:   - name: volcano-sh\n380:     email: volcano-sh@example.com\n381: sources:\n382:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n383: ```\n384: \n385: ### _helpers.tpl Named Templates\n386: \n387: ```yaml\n388: {{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n389: {{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n390: {{- end -}}\n391: \n392: {{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n393: {{- if .Values.fullnameOverride -}}\n394: {{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n395: {{- else -}}\n396: {{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride -}}\n397: {{- if contains $name .Release.Name -}}\n398: {{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n399: {{- else -}}\n400: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n401: {{- end -}}\n402: {{- end -}}\n403: {{- end -}}\n404: \n405: {{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\n406: app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n407: app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n408: app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n409: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n410: {{- end -}}\n411: \n412: {{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\n413: app: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n414: {{- end -}}\n415: ```\n416: \n417: ### Required Value Validation Pattern\n418: \n419: ```yaml\n420: {{- if not .Values.redis.addr }}\n421: {{- fail \"redis.addr must be provided\" }}\n422: {{- end }}\n423: ```\n424: \n425: ### Conditional RBAC Rendering Pattern\n426: \n427: ```yaml\n428: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n429: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n430: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n431: {{- end }}\n432: # RBAC resources...\n433: {{- end }}\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ---\n437: \n438: ## Implementation Timeline\n439: \n440: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n441: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n442: | Phase 1: Foundation | T1.1-T1.3 | Pending | 0% |\n443: | Phase 2: WorkloadManager | T2.1-T2.8 | Pending | 0% |\n444: | Phase 3: Router | T3.1-T3.9 | Pending | 0% |\n445: | Phase 4: RBAC | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n446: | Phase 5: Volcano Scheduler | T5.1-T5.3 | Pending | 0% |\n447: | Phase 6: CRDs | T6.1-T6.4 | Pending | 0% |\n448: | Phase 7: Validation | T7.1-T7.3 | Pending | 0% |\n449: | Phase 8: Tests | T8.1-T8.8 | Pending | 0% |\n450: \n451: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/47 tasks)**\n452: \n453: ---\n454: \n455: ## References\n456: \n457: - Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md`\n458: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`\n459: - Proposal: `changes/AR-030/proposal.md`\n460: - deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n461: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n462: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n463: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n\n(End of file - total 463 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Chart Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with chart metadata\n  - Purpose: Define chart name, version, appVersion, and metadata","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775884623026,"end":1775884623064}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884623072,"sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","part":{"id":"prt_d7af8dc8f001d1PUJyQ8WY5cKJ","messageID":"msg_d7af8b8b6001mDOtd5gsCpruZm","sessionID":"ses_285076336ffep1wj9l1c6SiZ51","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c8b61fadbb1e4b2389c1f248336689c2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: **Module:** `manifests`  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Helm Chart metadata file with correct API version and component information.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n22: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` is created\n23: - **WHEN** the file is written\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n25:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n26:   - `name: agentcube`\n27:   - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n28:   - `version: 0.1.0` (chart version)\n29:   - `appVersion: 1.0.0` (application version)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Chart dependencies\n32: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml defines optional subchart dependencies\n33: - **WHEN** external charts are needed\n34: - **THEN** dependencies SHALL be listed in `dependencies` array with `name`, `version`, `repository`, and optional `condition` for enabling/disabling\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: values.yaml default configuration\n39: \n40: The system SHALL provide comprehensive default values for all deployable components.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Global values section\n43: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` is created\n44: - **WHEN** global configuration is defined\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n46:   - `imagePullSecrets: []` (array of secret names for private registries)\n47:   - `nameOverride: \"\"` (partial name override)\n48:   - `fullnameOverride: \"\"` (full name override)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Redis connection values\n51: - **GIVEN** redis configuration is needed for router and workloadmanager\n52: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines redis settings\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n54:   - `redis.addr: \"\"` (Redis address, format `host:port`)\n55:   - `redis.password: \"\"` (Redis password, empty for no auth)\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Router deployment values\n58: - **GIVEN** router component is configurable\n59: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines router section\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n61:   - `router.replicas: 1` (int)\n62:   - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` (string)\n63:   - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n64:   - `router.image.tag: latest` (string)\n65:   - `router.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n66:   - `router.service.port: 8080` (int)\n67:   - `router.service.targetPort: 8080` (int)\n68:   - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n69:   - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n70:   - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n71:   - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n72:   - `router.config: {}` (object)\n73:   - `router.extraEnv: []` (array)\n74:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (string)\n75:   - `router.rbac.create: false` (bool)\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager deployment values\n78: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager component is configurable\n79: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines workloadmanager section\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n81:   - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1` (int)\n82:   - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` (string)\n83:   - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n84:   - `workloadmanager.image.tag: latest` (string)\n85:   - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n86:   - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080` (int)\n87:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n88:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n89:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n90:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n91:   - `workloadmanager.extraEnv: []` (array)\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler optional values\n94: - **GIVEN** volcano scheduler is an optional component\n95: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines volcano.scheduler section\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n97:   - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (bool, disabled by default)\n98:   - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1` (int)\n99:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` (string)\n100:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n101:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: latest` (string)\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager Deployment template\n106: \n107: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Deployment metadata\n110: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n111: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n112: - **THEN** Deployment metadata SHALL include:\n113:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n114:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n115:   - `labels` using helper templates\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Deployment spec replicas\n118: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager Deployment is templated\n119: - **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n120: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Deployment container image\n123: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager container is defined\n124: - **WHEN** image values are set\n125: - **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n126:   - `image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"`\n127:   - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}`\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Deployment environment variables\n130: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs namespace and redis config\n131: - **WHEN** env section is templated\n132: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n133:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n134:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n135:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n136:   - Extra env from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Deployment container args\n139: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs port configuration\n140: - **WHEN** args are templated\n141: - **THEN** args SHALL include:\n142:   - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n143:   - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty string for default)\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Deployment resources\n146: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager has configurable resources\n147: - **WHEN** resources section is templated\n148: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.resources }}`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Deployment health probes\n151: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs health endpoints\n152: - **WHEN** liveness and readiness probes are defined\n153: - **THEN** both SHALL be HTTP GET:\n154:   - `path: /health`\n155:   - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n156:   - liveness: `initialDelaySeconds: 10`, `periodSeconds: 10`\n157:   - readiness: `initialDelaySeconds: 5`, `periodSeconds: 5`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Deployment imagePullSecrets optional\n160: - **GIVEN** `imagePullSecrets` array in global values\n161: - **WHEN** array is non-empty\n162: - **THEN** `spec.template.spec.imagePullSecrets` SHALL be rendered from values\n163: - **WHEN** array is empty\n164: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` section SHALL be omitted\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager Service template\n169: \n170: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager Service with configurable type and port.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Service metadata\n173: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager Service is rendered\n174: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n175: - **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n176:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n177:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n178:   - `labels` matching Deployment\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Service spec\n181: - **GIVEN** Service is templated\n182: - **WHEN** service values are defined\n183: - **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n184:   - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n185:   - `ports` array with:\n186:     - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n187:     - `targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n188:     - `protocol: TCP`\n189:     - `name: http`\n190:   - `selector: app: workloadmanager`\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: Router Deployment template\n195: \n196: The system SHALL template Router Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment including Redis and WorkloadManager URLs.\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n199: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` is rendered\n200: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n201: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL have:\n202:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n203:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n204:   - `labels` using helper templates\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Router Deployment replicas\n207: - **GIVEN** router Deployment is templated\n208: - **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n209: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.replicas }}`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName conditional\n212: - **GIVEN** router Deployment needs optional service account\n213: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n214: - **THEN** `spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName` SHALL be set to that value\n215: - **WHEN** value is empty\n216: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be omitted (uses default)\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Router container image\n219: - **GIVEN** router container is defined\n220: - **WHEN** image values are set\n221: - **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n222:   - `image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"`\n223:   - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Router container port\n226: - **GIVEN** router exposes HTTP port\n227: - **WHEN** container ports are defined\n228: - **THEN** `ports` SHALL include:\n229:   - `containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n230:   - `protocol: TCP`\n231:   - `name: http`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Router environment variables\n234: - **GIVEN** router needs namespace, redis, and workloadmanager config\n235: - **WHEN** env section is templated\n236: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n237:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n238:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n239:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n240:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n241:   - Extra env from `{{ .Values.router.extraEnv }}`\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Router container args\n244: - **GIVEN** router needs port and debug configuration\n245: - **WHEN** args are templated\n246: - **THEN** args SHALL include:\n247:   - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n248:   - `--debug`\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Router resources\n251: - **GIVEN** router has configurable resources\n252: - **WHEN** resources section is templated\n253: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.router.resources }}`\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Router health probes\n256: - **GIVEN** router needs separate liveness and readiness endpoints\n257: - **WHEN** probes are defined\n258: - **THEN** probes SHALL be HTTP GET on `{{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`:\n259:   - liveness: `path: /health/live`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n260:   - readiness: `path: /health/ready`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### Requirement: Router Service template\n265: \n266: The system SHALL template Router Service with configurable type, port, and targetPort.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Router Service metadata\n269: - **GIVEN** Router Service is rendered\n270: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n271: - **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n272:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n273:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n274:   - `labels` matching Deployment\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Router Service spec\n277: - **GIVEN** Service is templated\n278: - **WHEN** service values are defined\n279: - **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n280:   - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n281:   - `ports` array with:\n282:     - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n283:     - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n284:     - `protocol: TCP`\n285:     - `name: http`\n286:   - `selector: app: agentcube-router`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n291: \n292: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding).\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager\n295: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n296: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n297: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n298:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n299:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: ClusterRole for WorkloadManager\n302: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs cluster-scoped permissions\n303: - **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n304: - **THEN** ClusterRole `workloadmanager` SHALL have rules:\n305: \n306: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n307: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n308: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n309: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n310: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n311: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n312: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n313: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n314: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n315: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n316: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n317: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n318: | `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n319: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n320: | `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding for WorkloadManager\n323: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n324: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n325: - **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding `workloadmanager` SHALL have:\n326:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount `workloadmanager` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n327:   - `roleRef`: ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n328: \n329: ---\n330: \n331: ### Requirement: Router RBAC template (conditional)\n332: \n333: The system SHALL conditionally template Router RBAC resources when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n336: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n337: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n338: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n339: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n340: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name derivation\n343: - **GIVEN** router RBAC is enabled\n344: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n345: - **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL be that value\n346: - **WHEN** value is empty\n347: - **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL default to `agentcube-router`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Router Role permissions\n350: - **GIVEN** router needs namespace-scoped secret access\n351: - **WHEN** Role is templated\n352: - **THEN** Role SHALL have rules:\n353:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n354:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n355:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n358: - **GIVEN** router Role needs binding\n359: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n360: - **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL reference:\n361:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with derived name in release namespace\n362:   - `roleRef`: Role with same name\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: Volcano Agent Scheduler template (conditional)\n367: \n368: The system SHALL conditionally template Volcano Agent Scheduler when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler conditional rendering\n371: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` exists\n372: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}` is `true`\n373: - **THEN** all scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n374: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n375: - **THEN** no scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount\n378: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n379: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n380: - **THEN** `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ConfigMap\n383: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n384: - **WHEN** ConfigMap is templated\n385: - **THEN** ConfigMap `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` SHALL have:\n386:   - `data.agent-scheduler.conf` containing scheduler configuration with `actions: [\"allocate\"]` and `tiers`\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ClusterRole\n389: - **GIVEN** scheduler needs broad cluster permissions\n390: - **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n391: - **THEN** ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have rules covering:\n392:   - `apiextensions.k8s.io/customresourcedefinitions`\n393:   - `\"\"` (core): `events, pods, pods/status, pods/binding, persistentvolumeclaims, persistentvolumes, namespaces, services, replicationcontrollers, resourcequotas, nodes, configmaps`\n394:   - `storage.k8s.io`: storage-related resources\n395:   - `policy/poddisruptionbudgets`\n396:   - `scheduling.k8s.io/priorityclasses`\n397:   - `scheduling.volcano.sh/podgroups`\n398:   - `apps`: daemonsets, replicasets, statefulsets\n399:   - `coordination.k8s.io/leases`\n400:   - `resource.k8s.io`: resource claims\n401:   - `shard.volcano.sh/nodeshards`\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Deployment\n404: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n405: - **WHEN** Deployment is templated\n406: - **THEN** Deployment `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have:\n407:   - `replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}`\n408:   - `image` from volcano.scheduler.image values\n409:   - `args` including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n410:   - `securityContext` for container\n411:   - `volumes` for config and emptyDir\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Service\n414: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n415: - **WHEN** Service is templated\n416: - **THEN** Service `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` SHALL have:\n417:   - `port: 8080`\n418:   - `annotations` for metrics\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: _helpers.tpl named templates\n423: \n424: The system SHALL provide helper templates for consistent naming and labeling across all resources.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: Name helper template\n427: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` is created\n428: - **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}` is invoked\n429: - **THEN** it SHALL return `.Chart.Name` or nameOverride\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Fullname helper template\n432: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines fullname\n433: - **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}` is invoked\n434: - **THEN** it SHALL return fully qualified resource name using release name + chart name + overrides\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Labels helper template\n437: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines labels\n438: - **WHEN** `{{ include \"agentcube.labels\" . }}` is invoked\n439: - **THEN** it SHALL return standard labels:\n440:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}`\n441:   - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n442:   - `app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}`\n443:   - `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}`\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Image helper template\n446: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines image helper\n447: - **WHEN** image path needs construction\n448: - **THEN** helper SHALL combine repository and tag with proper format\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: CRD files in crds/ directory\n453: \n454: The system SHALL ship CRD definitions that are installed before templates.\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: CRD directory location\n457: - **GIVEN** CRDs need to be bundled\n458: - **WHEN** chart is packaged\n459: - **THEN** CRDs SHALL be in `manifests/charts/base/crds/` directory\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD\n462: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` exists\n463: - **WHEN** CRD is installed\n464: - **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n465:   - `metadata.name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n466:   - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n467:   - `versions: v1alpha1` (served + storage)\n468:   - `scope: Namespaced`\n469:   - `spec.required: maxSessionDuration, podTemplate, sessionTimeout, targetPort`\n470:   - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`)\n471:   - `spec.sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`)\n472:   - `spec.targetPort` (array of port objects)\n473:   - `spec.podTemplate` (full PodSpec-shaped schema)\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD\n476: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` exists\n477: - **WHEN** CRD is installed\n478: - **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n479:   - `metadata.name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n480:   - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n481:   - `versions: v1alpha1`\n482:   - `scope: Namespaced`\n483:   - `spec.authMode` (enum `picod|none`, default `picod`)\n484:   - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (default `8h`)\n485:   - `spec.sessionTimeout` (default `15m`)\n486:   - `spec.template` (required: image, command, args, env, resources)\n487:   - `spec.warmPoolSize` (optional int32)\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ### Requirement: Helm lint and template validation\n492: \n493: The system SHALL pass Helm lint and produce valid rendered templates.\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n496: - **GIVEN** chart is complete\n497: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n498: - **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Template rendering produces valid YAML\n501: - **GIVEN** chart templates are complete\n502: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` is executed\n503: - **THEN** output SHALL be valid Kubernetes YAML for all enabled components\n504: \n505: #### Scenario: Template rendering with values override\n506: - **GIVEN** custom values are provided\n507: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is executed\n508: - **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values correctly\n509: \n510: ---\n511: \n512: ### Requirement: E2E deployment integration\n513: \n514: The system SHALL support E2E test deployment via helm upgrade --install.\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: E2E Helm install command\n517: - **GIVEN** E2E test environment (Kind cluster)\n518: - **WHEN** `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` deploys AgentCube\n519: - **THEN** command SHALL be:\n520:   ```bash\n521:   helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n522:     --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n523:     --create-namespace \\\n524:     --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n525:     --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n526:     --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n527:     --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n528:     --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n529:     --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n530:     --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n531:     --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n532:     --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n533:     --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n534:     --wait\n535:   ```\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: E2E local image references\n538: - **GIVEN** images are built and loaded into Kind\n539: - **WHEN** helm install runs\n540: - **THEN** image repository SHALL reference local image names (e.g., `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`) without registry prefix\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## Constants Summary\n545: \n546: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n547: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n548: | `DEFAULT_PORT` | `8080` | `values.yaml` | Default HTTP port for services |\n549: | `REDIS_PORT` | `6379` | `values.yaml` | Default Redis port |\n550: | `DEFAULT_REPLICAS` | `1` | `values.yaml` | Default replica count |\n551: | `DEFAULT_CPU_LIMIT` | `500m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU limit |\n552: | `DEFAULT_MEMORY_LIMIT` | `512Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory limit |\n553: | `DEFAULT_CPU_REQUEST` | `100m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU request |\n554: | `DEFAULT_MEMORY_REQUEST` | `128Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory request |\n555: | `DEFAULT_IMAGE_PULL_POLICY` | `IfNotPresent` | `values.yaml` | Default pull policy |\n556: | `DEFAULT_SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `15m` | CRDs | Default session timeout |\n557: | `DEFAULT_MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `8h` | CRDs | Default max session duration |\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Dependencies Summary\n562: \n563: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n564: |---------|---------|---------|\n565: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n566: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD resources |\n567: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `main` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n568: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## File Changes Summary\n573: \n574: | File | Action | Description |\n575: |------|--------|-------------|\n576: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Added | Helm Chart metadata |\n577: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Added | Default configuration values |\n578: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Added | Named template helpers |\n579: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n580: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Added | Router Deployment + Service |\n581: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager RBAC resources |\n582: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Added | Router RBAC (conditional) |\n583: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Added | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n584: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | Added | AgentRuntime CRD definition |\n585: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | Added | CodeInterpreter CRD definition |\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - proposal.md — AR-030 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n592: - deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n593: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n594: - sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Component configuration details\n595: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n596: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## Validation Checklist\n601: \n602: - [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n603: - [ ] `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` produces valid YAML\n604: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment renders with correct image, env, probes\n605: - [ ] WorkloadManager Service renders with correct port and selector\n606: - [ ] Router Deployment renders with Redis and WorkloadManager URLs in env\n607: - [ ] Router Service renders with correct port mapping\n608: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has all required RBAC rules\n609: - [ ] Router RBAC renders conditionally when `router.rbac.create=true`\n610: - [ ] Volcano scheduler renders conditionally when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n611: - [ ] `_helpers.tpl` provides name, fullname, labels templates\n612: - [ ] CRD files are valid and match controller-gen output\n613: - [ ] E2E script can deploy with `helm upgrade --install`\n614: - [ ] Custom values override defaults correctly\n\n(End of file - total 614 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Helm Chart metadata file with correct API version and component information.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884623027,"end":1775884623068}}}}
